HEADWORD: Consistorian
<hw>Con`sis*to"rian</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <def>Pertaining to
a Presbyterian consistory; -- a contemptuous term of 17th century
controversy.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>You fall next on the <qex>consistorian</qex> schismatics; for so
you call Presbyterians.</q> <rj><qau>Milton.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Consistory</ent>⟦br⟧
